## Future Independence: Core Engineering Principles
If you encounter UI layout conflicts in Linux desktop environments, trace the "Source of Truth" for the failing component.
* `xrandr --transform` dictates the X Server's raw pixel mapping.
* `xrandr --mode` dictates the hardware truth presented to the Window Manager.

When a monolithic compositor (like GNOME Mutter) refuses to respect spatial constraints from lower-level software flags, you must manipulate the hardware mode directly to establish a new mathematical truth for the compositor before altering the rendering matrix beneath it.
